Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: duckbotos-computer-use
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: python3.12, python3-pip, git, xdotool, scrot, gnome-screenshot,
         weston (>= 10),
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: duckbotos-cua-bridge,
            trycua-driver,
Suggests: adb,
Description: DuckBotOS desktop control — Newest Desktop Control (Lobster Edition)
 Installs Duckets' MIT-licensed `desktop-control-lobster-edition-skill`
 MCP server for full desktop control of the Weston kiosk session:
 .
   • Screenshots, mouse, keyboard, clipboard (PyAutoGUI + AT-SPI2)
   • App launching, window activation, file I/O, terminal
   • Android ADB control (if adb installed)
   • Codex Computer Use detection (macOS)
   • 20+ MCP tools registered automatically with Hermes/OpenClaw
 .
 Installed at /opt/duckbotos/desktop-control/
 MCP entrypoint: node /opt/duckbotos/desktop-control/src/server.js
 .
 Service: /etc/systemd/system/duckbotos-desktop-control.service
          (runs as the kiosk user, AUTO-START on boot)
 .
 Wires into Hermes (port 9119) and OpenClaw (port 18789) automatically:
   • Hermes: posts MCP config to ~/.hermes/mcp-servers.json
   • OpenClaw: patches openclaw.json → plugins.entries.desktop-control
   • Both: enables plugin and restarts the gateway service
 .
 Optional: install duckbotos-cua-bridge to expose trycua's cua-driver
 as an alternative backend (the Lobster Edition's `setup:cua` target).